-- U.S. Newspaper Ad-Sales Decline at Slower Pace in Third Quarter, Down 5.4%
-- B y   V i l l e   H e i s k a n e n
-- 2010-12-02T15:48:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-02/u-s-newspaper-ad-sales-decline-at-slower-pace-in-third-quarter-down-5-4-.html
Advertising revenue at U.S. newspaper
publishers declined at a slowing pace in the third quarter, the
Newspaper Association of America said.  Ad revenue dropped 5.4 percent last quarter, compared with
a 28 percent slump a year earlier, the association said on its
website. Print ad revenue fell 7.1 percent and online ad sales
rose 11 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ville Heiskanen at 
 vheiskanen@bloomberg.net  